18 Section 2. Section 50-49-203, MCA, is amended to read:
19 "50-49-203. Exemptions from regulations -- fee -- transactions -- information required --
20 exceptions. (1) (a) A state agency or an agency of a political subdivision of the state may not require licensure,
21 permitting, certification, packaging, labeling, testing, sampling, or inspection that pertains to the preparation,
22 serving, use, consumption, delivery, or storage of homemade food or a homemade food product under this part.
23 (b) (i) This part does not preclude an agency from providing assistance, consultation, or inspection
24 requested by a producer.
25 (ii) The department of public health and human services shall collect for each inspection requested
26 under subsection (1)(b)(i) a $25 fee from the requesting producer. The fees collected under this subsection
27 (1)(b)(ii) must be deposited in the local board of inspection fund account created in 50-2-108.
28 (c) A producer is not:
